This guide explains how to install and run Kubernetes (Minikube) on Windows step by step.

1Ô∏è‚É£ Prerequisites

Windows 10/11 with Docker Desktop or Hyper-V enabled

PowerShell or Command Prompt

Internet connection

2Ô∏è‚É£ Install Minikube

Download the Minikube binary and install:

choco install minikube -y


Check installation:

minikube version

3Ô∏è‚É£ Install kubectl (Kubernetes CLI)

Download kubectl.exe:

curl -LO "https://dl.k8s.io/release/v1.33.1/bin/windows/amd64/kubectl.exe"


Replace v1.33.1 with the latest stable version.
Check latest version here:
üëâ https://dl.k8s.io/release/stable.txt

Move kubectl.exe to C:\Windows\System32\ so it‚Äôs available globally.

Verify installation:

kubectl version --client

4Ô∏è‚É£ Start Minikube Cluster
Start single-node cluster with Docker driver:
minikube start --driver=docker

Start multi-node cluster (3 nodes):
minikube start --driver=docker --nodes=3


If an old cluster exists with another driver (e.g., Hyper-V), delete it first:

minikube delete

5Ô∏è‚É£ Check Cluster Status

Check Minikube status:

minikube status


Check available nodes:

kubectl get nodes


Example output:

NAME       STATUS   ROLES           AGE   VERSION
minikube   Ready    control-plane   5m    v1.33.1

6Ô∏è‚É£ Check Pods & Control Plane Components

Check pods in the default namespace:

kubectl get pods


Output:

No resources found in default namespace.


Check control plane components in kube-system namespace:

kubectl get pods -n kube-system


Example output:

NAME                               READY   STATUS    RESTARTS   AGE
coredns-78fcd69978-d8g2m           1/1     Running   0          10m
etcd-minikube                      1/1     Running   0          10m
kube-apiserver-minikube            1/1     Running   0          10m
kube-controller-manager-minikube   1/1     Running   0          10m
kube-scheduler-minikube            1/1     Running   0          10m
kube-proxy-abcde                   1/1     Running   0          10m
storage-provisioner                1/1     Running   0          10m

7Ô∏è‚É£ Useful Commands Recap
Command	Description
minikube start --driver=docker	Start Minikube with Docker driver
minikube start --driver=docker --nodes=3	Start Minikube with 3 nodes
minikube delete	Delete existing cluster
kubectl version --client	Check kubectl version
kubectl get nodes	List cluster nodes
kubectl get pods	List pods in default namespace
kubectl get pods -n kube-system	List system/control-plane pods
minikube status	Show Minikube cluster status

üî• Now you have Kubernetes running on Windows with Minikube & kubectl!
